quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  21,11,How many nations We have destroyed because of their iniquities and replaced them by other nations
  21,12,"When they felt that Our punishment was coming, they took to their heels and fled"
  21,13,"They were told: \"Do not run away. Return to your luxuries of life and to your homes, so that you may be asked questions"
  21,14,"They replied: \"Woe to us! Indeed we were wrongdoers"
  21,15,"They kept on repeating that statement till We mowed them down, leaving no spark of life in them"
  21,16,Our creation of the heavens and the earth and all that lies between them is not a game
  21,17,"Had We meant to make it a play ground, We would have done it by Ourself, without giving you discretion to do right and wrong, had We ever done so"
  21,18,"Nay! We give falsehood a violent blow with the Truth to knock it out and behold! Falsehood vanishes away. Woe be to you, for all the false gods you have invented"
  21,19,"To Him belongs all that exists in the heavens and in the earth; and the angels, who are in His very presence, are not too proud to serve Him, nor do they feel wearied of His service"
  21,20,They glorify Him night and day; and do not pause
  21,21,"Have the earthly deities, that they have taken for worship, the power to raise the dead"
  21,22,"If there were other gods in the heavens or in the earth besides Allah, both the heavens and earth would have been in a state of disorder. Glory be to Allah, the Lord of the Throne, absolutely free is He from the falsehood that they attribute to Him"
  21,23,"He is accountable to none about what He does, but they are accountable to Him"
  21,24,"Even then, have they taken other deities for worship besides Him? Ask them: \"Show us your proof: here is this reminder (Al-Qurâ€™an) for the people of my time and it also contains the reminder of those before me.\" But most of them have no knowledge of Reality, and that is why they have turned away"